=Episode 11=

3
00:00:41,779 --> 00:00:44,320
(One year ago)

4
00:01:05,960 --> 00:01:06,760
Mr. Fang,

5
00:01:06,760 --> 00:01:07,720
when did you come back?

6
00:01:07,720 --> 00:01:08,520
Please sit down.

7
00:01:11,920 --> 00:01:13,120
Why are you here all alone?

8
00:01:13,400 --> 00:01:14,200
Where is Mr. Wang?

9
00:01:15,480 --> 00:01:16,560
Mr. Wang has an emergency

10
00:01:16,560 --> 00:01:17,720
at home these days.

11
00:01:17,720 --> 00:01:19,320
So I am watching over the store for him.

12
00:01:20,240 --> 00:01:21,560
You should go back and rest.

13
00:01:21,960 --> 00:01:22,720
Don't sit here.

14
00:01:22,720 --> 00:01:23,560
It's quite chilly.

15
00:01:24,840 --> 00:01:26,040
At the pier, I asked

16
00:01:26,040 --> 00:01:27,360
about your boat's schedule.

17
00:01:27,440 --> 00:01:28,760
I knew you would come back late.

18
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:29,720
I was afraid

19
00:01:29,720 --> 00:01:30,480
you would starve

20
00:01:30,480 --> 00:01:31,440
when you were back.

21
00:01:31,600 --> 00:01:32,360
So I prepared these

22
00:01:32,360 --> 00:01:33,680
in advance to wait

23
00:01:33,680 --> 00:01:34,760
for you to come back.

24
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:40,800
They seem to have gotten cold.

25
00:01:40,800 --> 00:01:41,560
I'll heat them up.

26
00:01:41,560 --> 00:01:42,240
No need.

27
00:01:42,880 --> 00:01:43,760
I'm actually hungry.

28
00:01:43,760 --> 00:01:44,600
I'll just eat them.

29
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:46,560
Then have a taste.

30
00:01:46,560 --> 00:01:47,240
Okay.

31
00:01:58,400 --> 00:01:59,160
What's wrong?

32
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:00,400
You don't like it?

33
00:02:02,520 --> 00:02:03,320
My mother used

34
00:02:04,360 --> 00:02:05,920
to make this for me when I was little.

35
00:02:06,400 --> 00:02:07,840
Ever since she passed away,

36
00:02:08,280 --> 00:02:09,560
I have never eaten it again.

37
00:02:10,160 --> 00:02:11,960
I never expected
to taste it again today.

38
00:02:12,680 --> 00:02:13,480
Really?

39
00:02:22,440 --> 00:02:23,240
Let's eat together.

40
00:02:24,040 --> 00:02:24,840
Okay.

41
00:02:29,880 --> 00:02:30,680
Here.

42
00:02:30,960 --> 00:02:31,760
Thank you.

43
00:02:33,299 --> 00:02:38,112
♪Yet it cannot cover the past♪

44
00:02:44,240 --> 00:02:45,120
Mr. Fang.

45
00:02:45,600 --> 00:02:46,720
I made it myself.

46
00:02:46,800 --> 00:02:47,760
Please try it.

47
00:02:50,960 --> 00:02:51,760
Mr. Wang.

48
00:02:54,640 --> 00:02:55,440
Young master.

49
00:02:55,520 --> 00:02:56,320
She made this.

50
00:02:56,920 --> 00:02:57,920
You made it?

51
00:02:57,920 --> 00:02:58,760
Try some.

52
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:00,360
Alright, then.

53
00:03:03,059 --> 00:03:04,832
♪You've given my days a purpose♪

54
00:03:04,832 --> 00:03:08,480
♪A grand dream, monumental and vast♪

55
00:03:09,920 --> 00:03:10,760
You have some too.

56
00:03:11,560 --> 00:03:12,400
Okay.

57
